==English==
===Etymology 1===
Name of the Biblical character [[w:Abel|Abel]] + [[-ian]].

====Noun====
#(''ecclesiastical history'') One of a [[sect]] in fourth-century Africa mentioned by St. [[Augustine]], who states that they married but lived in [[continence]] after the manner, as they [[claim]]ed, of Abel.

====Synonyms====
*[[Abelite]]
*[[Abelonian]]

====Translations====
*French: [[abélien]], [[abélite]]

===Etymology 2===
Name of the Norwegian mathematician [[w:Niels Henrik Abel|Abel]] + [[-ian]].

===Adjective===
#(''mathematics'') Of a [[group]], having a defining [[operation]] that is [[commutative]].

